CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 27, 1945, pg. 28, reads: "Married - Dorothy M. Georgia, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Charles Georgia, and James R. Dorsett, son of Mr. and Mrs. Hazel Dorsett, Sturdevant, of the North Side, were married Saturday, Oct. 13, at the Buena Vista ME Church. Mr. and Mrs. Dorsett will reside at 414 Armandale Street. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom James R. Dorsett in tuxedo and bride Dorothy M. Georgia in gown with sweetheart neckline, posed in front of dark curtain in Harris Studio
